      "description": "This E46 M3 is a driver-focused example featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine equipped with individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and a mechanical limited-slip differential for superior power delivery. Critical preventative maintenance has been proactively addressed, including rear subframe reinforcement and a VANOS overhaul, ensuring the chassis remains rigid under high lateral loads. The suspension geometry is well-sorted with refreshed bushings, maintaining the sharp turn-in and communicative steering rack the M-division is known for. While the aesthetics show honest signs of road use, the mechanical vitals are robust and the throttle response remains exceptionally crisp.",
